<h1>Problem 929 - 2019 IMOSL, A4</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Let \(n\geqslant 2\) be a positive integer and \(a_1,a_2, \ldots ,a_n\) be real numbers such that\[a_1+a_2+\dots+a_n=0.\]Define the set \(A\) by \[A=\left\{(i, j)\,|\,1 \leqslant i < j \leqslant n,\left|a_{i}-a_{j}\right| \geqslant 1\right\}\] Prove that, if \(A\) is not empty, then \[\sum_{(i, j) \in A} a_{i} a_{j}<0.\]</p>
